results.name: Smallest number beginning with 9 and having exactly n distinct prime divisors.
program: (PARI) a(n) = {i = prod(i=1, n, prime(i)); while ((digits(i)[1] != 9) || (omega(i)!= n), i++); i;} \\ _Michel Marcus_, Sep 14 2013
